  "prompt": "What is the best way to withdraw money from freelancer.com in indian currency?",
  "response": "There are several ways to withdraw money from Freelancer.com in Indian currency:\n\n1. Bank Transfer (NEFT/IMPS)\n- Most common and recommended method\n- Direct transfer to your Indian bank account\n- Low transaction fees\n- Typically takes 2-5 business days\n- Requires linking your bank account details on Freelancer.com\n\n2. PayPal\n- Convert earnings to Indian Rupees\n- Transfer to linked Indian bank account\n- Some transaction fees may apply\n- Relatively quick transfer\n\n3. Skrill\n- Online payment platform\n- Can transfer to Indian bank account\n- Competitive exchange rates\n- Lower fees compared to some other methods\n\n4. TransferWise (now Wise)\n- Good exchange rates\n- Low transfer fees\n- Quick and reliable transfer\n\n5. Cryptocurrency\n- Can convert earnings to Bitcoin or other cryptocurrencies\n- Transfer to Indian exchanges\n- More complex process\n\nRecommended steps:\n- Verify your Freelancer.com account\n- Complete KYC requirements\n- Link your preferred payment method\n- Choose the method with lowest fees and fastest transfer\n\nBest overall recommendation: Bank transfer (NEFT/IMPS) or PayPal for most Indian freelancers.",
